Underground fire in Joburg CBD trips power JOHANNESBURG - Power in the Johannesburg CBD has been repaired and restoration to other parts of the city has begun. The outages were caused by a fire that broke out in the city's underground tunnels housing power cables at the Fordsburg substation. READ | Joburg south residents still in the dark following substation fire It has since been extinguished. It's still not known when the power will be fully restored. Firefighters had been battling to access the tunnel as the fire was too dangerous.